msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: sources/gamemaster_rules/monsters/spy.md:11
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"**Armor Class** 12    \n"
"**Hit Points** 27 (6d8)    \n"
"**Speed** 30 ft. \n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: sources/gamemaster_rules/monsters/spy.md:15
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"| STR     | DEX     | CON     | INT     | WIS     | CHA     |\n"
"|---------|---------|---------|---------|---------|---------|\n"
"| 10 (+0) | 15 (+2) | 10 (+0) | 12 (+1) | 14 (+2) | 16 (+3) |   \n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: sources/gamemaster_rules/monsters/spy.md:20
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"**Skills** Deception +5, Insight +4, Investigation +5, Perception +6, "
"Persuasion +5, Sleight of Hand +4, Stealth +4    \n"
"**Senses** passive Perception 16    \n"
"**Languages** any two languages    \n"
"**Challenge** 1 (200 XP) \n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: sources/gamemaster_rules/monsters/spy.md:23
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"**Cunning Action.** On each of its turns, the spy can use a bonus action to "
"take the Dash, Disengage, or Hide action.    \n"
"**Sneak Attack (1/Turn).** The spy deals an extra 7 (2d6) damage when it "
"hits a target with a weapon attack and has advantage on the attack roll, or "
"when the target is within 5 feet of an ally of the spy that isn't "
"incapacitated and the spy doesn't have disadvantage on the attack roll. \n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: sources/gamemaster_rules/monsters/spy.md:28
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"### Actions \n"
"**Multiattack.** The spy makes two melee attacks.    \n"
"**Shortsword.** _Melee Weapon Attack:_ +4 to hit, reach 5 ft., one "
"target. _Hit:_ 5 (1d6 + 2) piercing damage.    \n"
"**Hand Crossbow.** _Ranged Weapon Attack:_ +4 to hit, range 30/120 ft., one "
"target. _Hit:_ 5 (1d6 + 2) piercing damage. \n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: sources/gamemaster_rules/monsters/spy.md:30
msgid ""
"### Description Rulers, nobles, merchants, guildmasters, and other wealthy "
"individuals use spies to gain the upper hand in a world of cutthroat "
"politics. A spy is trained to secretly gather information. Loyal spies would "
"rather die than divulge information that could compromise them or their "
"employers."
msgstr ""
